 earliest of Newton's drafts, likely written in 1669-73 and certainly not\nlater than 1683/4. A comparison of the two drafts of Yahuda 24E shows that in\nthe later one, Newton changed his allegiance from St. John's chronology of the\nPassion to that shown in the synoptic gospels.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 23 Oct 2008 22:25:47 GMT"}],"update_date":"2008-10-27"}
